Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

To make your stock, add the @boiled water{750%ml}(for the risotto) to a #medium saucepan{} on high heat. Stir in the @vegetable stock paste{15%g}. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to the lowest setting.

Halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1} into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled) or use a #garlic press{}. Halve any large @tenderstem broccoli{150%g} stems lengthways.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the shallot and cook until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and @sun-dried tomato paste{50%g}, then cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @risotto rice{175%g}, stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

To make your risotto, stir a ladle of stock into the rice. When the stock has been absorbed by the rice, stir in another ladle of stock. Keep the pan on medium heat and continue stirring in stock, letting it absorb each time. The cooking time should take ~{20-25%minutes} and your risotto is done when your rice is 'al dente' - cooked through but with a tiny bit of firmness left in the middle.

When the risotto has about 10 mins cooking time left, pop the broccoli and @baby plum tomatoes{125%g} onto a #large baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Roast on the middle shelf of your oven until tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

When the risotto is cooked, remove from the heat and mix in the @butter{20%g} and @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

When the veg is roasted, serve the risotto in #bowls{} with the roasted broccoli and tomatoes on top.

Finish with a drizzle of the @balsamic glaze{12%ml}. Enjoy!